edas#SlideSet: The Document is the parent of the SlideSet which belongs to the event. The ConferenceEvent is a non-Academic event and is the child of the ConferenceEvent.
edas#Review: Review is the parent of Document which is part of the programme. Paper is also part of the programme and has the ReviewRating.
edas#Programme: The Document relating to ConferenceSession is the parent of the Document which is a child of the SlideSet.
edas#Paper: Document is the parent of Paper and SlideSet.
edas#MealMenu: The document MealMenu is the parent of MealEvent which is a non-academic event. It is also the parent of Paper which is reviewed by a person who has a personal review history. The document is related to the Conference which is equivalent to TwoLevelConference.
edas#Document: MealMenu is a document that is the parent of MealMenu.
edas#Topic: The SignalProcessingTopic is the parent of the Conference which is the equivalent of TwoLevelConference. It is also the parent of Thing and is the child of SignalProcessingTopic.
edas#ConferenceEvent: ConferenceEvent is the parent of MealEvent and ConferenceDinner. MealEvent is the child of ConferenceDinner and ConferenceEvent.
edas#Call: CallForManuscripts and CallForPapers are both children of CallForManuscripts.
edas#ReviewRating: ReviewRating is the equivalent of WeekRejectRating and is a child of RejectRating.
edas#Organization: The organization isProviderOf and is the parent of TravelGrant which is the sponsor of the Sponsorship.
edas#ReviewForm: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
edas#Conference: Conference is the parent of Thing and is the equivalent of SingleLevelConference.
edas#PersonalHistory: PersonalHistory is a child of PersonalPublicationHistory. It is the parent of PersonalReviewHistory which is a reviewer who is equivalent to a person.
edas#Sponsorship: TravelGrant is the parent of Sponsorship which is the child of TravelGrant.
edas#ReviewQuestion: ReviewQuestion is a child of TextualReviewQuestion and NumericalReviewQuestion.
edas#Person: The Conference is equivalent to a SingleLevelConference and a TwoLevelConference. The author is a member of the Conference.
edas#Country: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
edas#ConferenceSession: The ConferenceSession hasRelatedDocument. It is a document that is part of the review process. It is also part of the paper which is part of the ComputerNetworksTopic.
edas#ContactInformation: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
edas#Place: ConferenceEvent is the parent of BreakEvent, CoffeeBreak and ConferenceEvent. It is the parent of the ConferenceSession Document which is a part of the ConferenceEvent. The ConferenceEvent has a program called ConferenceEvent and is the parent of the Document which is part of the ConferenceEvent.
edas#WeekRejectRating: The WeekRejectRating is equivalent to the ReviewRating.
edas#AcceptRating: ReviewRating is the parent of ReviewRating and RejectRating. It is the child of AccpetIfRoomRating which is the parent of AccpetIfRoomRating.
edas#RejectRating: RejectRating is the parent of ReviewRating and AccpetIfRoomRating.
edas#MealEvent: BreakEvent and ConferenceDinner are both children of MealEvent. MealEvent and Reception are both children of MealEvent.
edas#NonAcademicEvent: The non-academic event is parented by the SessionChair and the Attendee. SocialEvent is also parented by the ConferenceEvent and the Attendee. The Document and SlideSet are both children of the ConferenceEvent.
edas#BreakEvent: BreakEvent is equivalent to CoffeeBreak and MealBreak.
edas#ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopi: The ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopic is the parent of Paper which is a child of PerformanceTopic and AcceptedPaper. Paper is also a child of ActivePaper which is a parent of Paper and related to an event.
edas#WirelessCommunicationsTopic: The WirelessCommunicationsTopic is parented to the MedicineTopic and the PowerlineTransmissionTopic.
edas#OperatingTopicsystems: OperatingTopicsystems is parented to CommunicationTheoryTopic and PerformanceTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksTopic: The ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic is the parent of the Paper and WirelessCommunicationsTopic. WithdrawnPaper is the parent of both Paper and Review.
edas#SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopi: The SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopic is parented to the RadioCommunicationsTopic and the SecurityTopic.
edas#CADTopic: CADTopic is parented to MultimediaTopic and CommunicationsTopic.
edas#MultimediaTopic: The MultimediaTopic is the parent of the Conference which is the parent of the Thing. The Conference is the parent of the ComputerArchitectureTopic which is a child of the Conference.
edas#CommunicationsTopic: The ComputerNetworksSensorTopic and the CommunicationsTopic are both parented by ComputerNetworksTopic. The MedicineTopic and the ComputerNetworksSensorTopic are both children of ComputerNetworksTopic.
edas#PowerlineTransmissionTopic: The PowerlineTransmissionTopic is the parent of the Paper which is a part of the AcademicEvent. The Paper is also the parent of the PerformanceTopic.
edas#AntennasTopic: The AntennasTopic is the parent of the Paper which is the child of the RadioCommunicationsTopic. The Paper is the child of the RejectedPaper which is the parent of the RejectedPaper which is the document relating to the Conference.
edas#PerformanceTopic: The PerformanceTopic is the parent of MicroelectronicsTopic and ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopic.
edas#SignalProcessingTopic: The SignalProcessingTopic is parented to the SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopic and the PowerlineTransmissionTopic.
edas#MicroelectronicsTopic: The MicroelectronicsTopic is parented to the WirelessCommunicationsTopic and the PowerlineTransmissionTopic.
edas#TestOnlyTopic: TestOnlyTopic is parented by both WirelessCommunicationsTopic and MobileComputingTopic.
edas#RadioCommunicationsTopic: The RadioCommunicationsTopic is the parent of the CryptographyTopic which is a part of the Conference. It is also the parent of Thing and is the parent of RadioCommunicationsTopic.
edas#ComputerArchitectureTopic: The Computer ArchitectureTopic is the parent of the SignalProcessingTopic and MobileComputingTopic.
edas#MedicineTopic: AntennasTopic is the parent of MedicineTopic which is a child of AntennasTopic. It is also the parent of Conference which is equivalent to a SingleLevelConference.
edas#SecurityTopic: TestOnlyTopic and ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic are both children of ComputerNetworksTopic. Both are parented by SecurityTopic and ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic.
edas#MobileComputingTopic: The MobileComputingTopic is the parent of the TestOnlyTopic which is the topic of the Conference. The Conference is the equivalent of a SingleLevelConference and its start date is the start date.
edas#CryptographyTopic: CADTopic is the parent of CryptographyTopic which is the topic of the conference. The conference has a topic called "Thing" and it's start date is the start date.
edas#CommunicationTheoryTopic: The CommunicationTheoryTopic is parented by the CryptographyTopic and the ComputerArchitectureTopic.
edas#ConferenceChair: CallForPapers and ActivePaper are both children of CallForReviews. The ConferenceChair is the parent of both CallForReviews and Paper which is being reviewed by the ConferenceChair.
edas#Author: The author hasRelatedPaper is the parent of Paper which is the child of PendingPaper and PublishedPaper.
edas#DiningPlace: The DiningPlace is the parent of the ConferenceEvent which is also the parent of the PaperPresentation event. The ConferenceEvent is also the parent of the AcademicEvent which is also the parent of the ConferenceEvent. The person who attended the ConferenceEvent is the equivalent of the person who reviewed the document.
edas#Presenter: RejectedPaper is the parent of RejectedPaper which is a child of Paper. It is the parent of RejectedPaper which is a paper that is equivalent to isWrittenBy.
edas#AcademiaOrganization: The parent organization of AcademiaOrganization is the GovernmentOrganization which is the parent organization of TravelGrant which is the parent organization of Sponsorship.
edas#IndustryOrganization: IndustryOrganization is parented by NGO isProviderOf which is a sponsor of TravelGrant which is a sponsor of TravelGrant.
edas#NGO: The NGO is parented by the organization IndustryOrganization which is the parent of the organization which provides Sponsorship.
edas#GovernmentOrganization: AcademiaOrganization is the parent organization of the Government Organization which is the parent organization of the NGO. AcademiaOrganization is the parent organization of the NGO.
edas#ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic: ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic is the parent of ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic and ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic: ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic is the parent of ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic. It is also the child of ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSensorTopic: The ComputerNetworksSensorTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksSensorTopic. The MultimediaTopic is the parent of the SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic: The ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic. It is also the parent of the Paper isTopicOf which was written by the author. The Paper is also the parent of the Conference which is the parent of the Thing.
edas#ComputerNetworksOpticalTopic: The ComputerNetworksOpticalTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic which is also a part of the CommunicationTheoryTopic. The Paper Topic is also a part of the ComputerNetworksTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic: The ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic is the parent of the MicroelectronicsTopic which is the topic of Paper. The Paper is the child of PublishedPaper and is the parent of the MicroelectronicsTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksManagementTopic: The ComputerNetworksManagementTopic is the parent of the ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic which is also the parent of the SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopic. The WirelessCommunicationsTopic is also the parent of ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic: ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic is the parent of ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic and ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic.
edas#ActivePaper: TPCMember is the parent of the child of SessionChair. The child of TPCMember is the child of SessionChair. The child of TPCMember is the child of SessionChair. The child of TPCMember is the child of SessionRating. The child of SessionRating is the child of RejectRating. The child of RejectRating is the child of RejectRating.
edas#PendingPaper: Paper is the parent of PendingPaper and RejectedPaper.
edas#WithdrawnPaper: WithdrawnPaper is the parent of Paper which is reviewed by TPCMember. The document is also the child of SlideSet which is also the child of TPCMember. The ConferenceChair is the child of TPCMember.
edas#RejectedPaper: TPCMember is the parent of the document RejectedPaper which is the parent of the Document. The document is also the child of the Conference Chair and the TPCMember is the parent of the person who is the reviewer.
edas#AcceptedPaper: The AcceptedPaper is the parent of both the Paper and the Review. The Paper is the parent of both the Paper and the Review. The Reviewer is a member of the Conference.
edas#PublishedPaper: TPCMember initiates the Call for Manuscripts. The call is initiated by the Conference Chair and is followed by a SlideSet. Paper is the parent of Paper and is being reviewed by TPCMember.
edas#Attendee: CallForManuscripts and CallForPapers are both children of the SessionChair. The SessionChair is the parent of the attendee. The Conference hasMembers and the CallForManuscripts is also a call for papers.
edas#CoffeeBreak: CoffeeBreak is the parent of BreakEvent and FreeTimeBreak. ConferenceEvent and ConferenceEvent are both children of ConferenceEvent.
edas#FreeTimeBreak: BreakEvent is the parent of BreakEvent and ConferenceEvent. ConferenceEvent is the parent of AcademicEvent and BreakEvent is the parent of BreakEvent.
edas#MealBreak: BreakEvent is the parent of BreakEvent and ConferenceEvent. BreakEvent is the parent of ConferenceEvent and ConferenceEvent. MealBreak is the equivalent of BreakEvent.
edas#Reviewer: PersonalReviewHistory is the parent of PersonalPublicationHistory which is the child of PersonalReviewHistory. It is the parent of PersonalReviewHistory which is the equivalent of Person.
edas#ClosingTalk: ClosingTalk is the parent of TalkEvent and WelcomeTalk.
edas#WelcomeTalk: WelcomeTalk is the parent of TalkEvent which is also the parent of OrganizationalMeeting. ConferenceEvent is also the parent of OrganizationalMeeting and has Attendee.
edas#TalkEvent: TPCMember is the parent of TPCMember who is reviewing a paper. TalkEvent is the child of ClosingTalk and is the parent of AcademicEvent. The call is initiated by TPCMember who is also the parent of TPCMember who is also the parent of TPCMember.
edas#SessionChair: The SessionChair is the parent of the person who initiates the call. This person is the equivalent of a Reviewer. The document AcademicEvent is the child of the document PaperPresentation which is related to AcceptedPaper.
edas#TPCMember: The TPCMember is the parent of the person who is the child of the SessionChair. The SessionChair initiates the Call for Papers and the Call forEvent which is part of the AcademicEvent.
edas#CallForPapers: CallForPapers is parented to ConferenceChair who is the TPCM member. The ConferenceChair is the parent of CallForManuscripts which is initiated by the ConferenceChair. The ConferenceChair is also the parent of the Conference Paper which is pending. The Paper is also the parent of the ConferenceChair who is reviewing the Paper.
edas#TextualReviewQuestion: ReviewQuestion is a child of TextualReviewQuestion and NumericalReviewQuestion.
edas#NumericalReviewQuestion: ReviewQuestion is the parent of NumericalReviewQuestion and TextualReviewQuestion.
edas#OrganizationalMeeting: OrganizationalMeeting is parent of both AcademicEvent and ClosingTalk. TalkEvent is the parent of both ConferenceEvent and SocialEvent. MealEvent and ConferenceEvent are both non-academic events.
edas#PaperPresentation: AcademicEvent is the parent of ConferenceEvent which is located at DiningPlace. The ConferenceEvent is the location of the ConferenceEvent and the Document is the parent of the ConferenceEvent. The Document is related to the ConferenceEvent and is the AcceptedPaper.
edas#Workshop: CallForPapers and CallForManuscripts are both children of ConferenceEvent. The ConferenceEvent is parented by the SessionChair and the ConferenceEvent hasAttendee. CallForPapers and CallForManuscripts are both children of ConferenceEvent.
edas#AcademicEvent: CallForManuscripts and CallForReviews are both children of CallForManuscripts. Both CallForReviews and AcademicEvent are both children of CallForManuscripts.
edas#PersonalPublicationHistory: PersonalHistory is the parent of PersonalPublicationHistory. It is the child of PersonalReviewHistory which is the reviewer of a paper. The reviewer is the equivalent of a person.
edas#Excursion: SocialEvent is the parent of Excursion and NonAcademicEvent. ConferenceEvent is also the parent of ConferenceEvent which is located in the same city.
edas#SocialEvent: SocialEvent is the parent of ConferenceEvent which has a program called "Programme". It is also the child of ConferenceEvent which is the parent of ConferenceEvent. ConferenceEvent is the parent of ConferenceEvent and ConferenceEvent is the child of ConferenceEvent and ConferenceEvent is the child of ConferenceEvent.
edas#CallForReviews: TPCMember is the parent of CallForReviews which is initiated by TPCMember. TPCMember is the parent of CallForPapers which is a child of SessionChair.
edas#PersonalReviewHistory: The PersonalReviewHistory is the parent of the PersonalReviewHistory which is a paper. It is also the parent of the PersonalPublicationHistory which is a document relating to the AcademicEvent. It is also the parent of the Paper which is being reviewed by the Reviewer.
edas#ConferenceVenuePlace: The ConferenceEvent is the parent of the ConferenceVenuePlace which is located at the isLocationOf ConferenceEvent. The ConferenceEvent is also the parent of the AcademicEvent and the ConferenceEvent hasRelatedDocument.
edas#CallForManuscripts: CallForManuscripts is initiated by the ConferenceChair who is the parent of the call. The call is also initiated by a reviewer who is a TPCM member.
edas#Reception: SocialEvent is the parent of both the ConferenceEvent and the AcademicEvent. SocialEvent is the parent of both ConferenceEvent and Excursion.
edas#MeetingRoomPlace: MeetingRoomPlace is the parent of ConferenceVenuePlace and is the child of MeetingRoomPlace.
edas#AccommodationPlace: ConferenceEvent is a non-academic event. It is also parented by ConferenceVenuePlace. The ConferenceChair is also a child of ConferenceEvent. The ConferenceEvent has an Attendee.
edas#RatedPapers: The parent of RatedPapers is ActivePaper which is the parent of the document MealMenu. ReviewRating is equivalent to RejectRating and is the child of Document.
edas#TravelGrant: TravelGrant is the parent of Sponsorship which is a child of TravelGrant.
edas#ConferenceDinner: MealEvent is the parent of ConferenceDinner and SlideSet. MealMenu is also the parent of Document which is a child of SlideSet.
